<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Imposing orders</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Imposing orders</p>
<p class="text">Once orders have been placed on an order site, items that have
  the imposition style property set (see <a href="items-properties.php" target="mainFrame">Editing
  an item's properties</a> and <a href="items-stylesimposition.php" target="mainFrame">Setting
  imposition styles</a>) will appear in the list when the Impose menu
  is selected in the VariaPrint&#8482; manager. </p>
<p class="text">To create an imposition file:</p>
<ol>
  <li class="text"> <span>Go to the Impose menu in the VariaPrint&#8482;
          manager</span></li>
  <li class="text">Select the imposition style you want to impose items for</li>
  <li class="text">Check the order items you want to impose</li>
  <li class="text">Enter the print run in the top right of the page and click
    the Go button</li>
  <li class="text">You may use the default arrangement of items for the imposition
    or rearrange the layout to suit your needs and then click the Download PDF
    button</li>
  <li class="text">After downloading and reviewing the imposition file, you may
    either discard it (if you decide to lay it out differently) or record it
    in the
    imposition
    history and create a docket that includes priority, due date, imposition
    layout, and shipping and order information. Once recorded, impostion files
    and dockets may be redownloaded from the &quot;Download Dockets / Impositions&quot;
    submenu under Impose.</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</body>
</html>
